data.title: Missing Wilton 13-Year-Old Found Safe
data.meta_description: Wilton Police say a missing 13-year-old boy has been found safe and is back with his family.
data.text:
Wilton Police say a missing 13-year-old boy has been found safe and is back with his family.

What Does He Look Like?

Gabriel Keith, 13 of Wilton is 5'7" tall, 110 pounds, and has blonde hair, and blue eyes.

When Was He Last Seen?

Keith was reported missing on Tuesday night, August 6th. Officials say he has been located and is safe.

Who Do We Call With Information?

Anyone with information about Gabriel's whereabouts is encouraged to contact the Wilton Police Department at 207-645-3876.

List of Missing Persons Cases in Maine

There are 35 people currently listed as missing here in Maine by the state police as of August 2024. If you recognize or have any information on the people listed here, please contact the police.

Gallery Credit: Sean McKenna

Mainers Advised to NOT Travel to These 9 Places

The United States Department of State regularly issues travel advisories for Americans to help keep them safe during their vacations. There are four levels of advisories: exercise normal precautions, exercise increased caution, reconsider travel and do not travel. These are nine of the 19 destinations under a Level 4: DO NOT TRAVEL advisory.
